---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Wall Coverings | Large-Format Porcelain & Decorative Panels in Venezuela"
  description="Premium wall coverings including large-format porcelain tiles, wall panels, natural stone, and microcement. Professional installation in Valencia, San Diego and Caracas."
  image="/images/revestimientos.webp"
  activePage="services"
>
  <header class="article-hero">
    <div class="hero-bg" style="background-image: url('/images/revestimientos.webp')"></div>
    <div class="hero-overlay"></div>
    <div class="hero-content">
      <a href="/en/services" class="back-link">← Back to Services</a>
      <span class="article-category">Specialized Service</span>
      <h1 class="article-title"><span class="line">Wall</span><span class="line gold">Coverings</span></h1>
      <p class="article-excerpt">Premium wall coverings that define the personality of each space with texture, depth, and incomparable aesthetic value.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="article-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="article-body">
        <p>Wall coverings have evolved from simple protective elements to becoming the protagonist of interior design. A well-selected and properly installed covering not only protects your walls from moisture and wear but defines each environment's personality, adds texture, depth, and incomparable aesthetic value.</p>

        <p>At ReformaT Venezuela, we work with the most in-demand materials on the current market, combining certified installation techniques with artisanal finishes. From large-format porcelain to decorative wall panels, every project is executed with millimeter precision to guarantee durability and premium aesthetics.</p>

        <img src="/images/revestimientos.webp" alt="Premium wall coverings by ReformaT Venezuela" loading="eager" fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" />

        <h2>Types of Wall Coverings We Install</h2>

        <h3>Large-Format Porcelain</h3>

        <p>The dominant trend in modern renovations. Pieces measuring 24x48 inches, 32x64 inches, or even 48x96 inch slabs that minimize joints, creating continuous, elegant surfaces. Available in finishes that imitate marble, concrete, wood, and natural stone with surprising realism.</p>

        <p><strong>Advantages:</strong> High scratch and stain resistance, easy cleaning, extreme durability, and luxury visual appearance.</p>

        <h3>Wall Panels (Decorative Panels)</h3>

        <p>Quick and versatile solution for renovating walls without wet construction. Made from PVC, moisture-resistant MDF, or composite materials, they're ideal for bedrooms, living rooms, bed headboards, and commercial spaces.</p>

        <p><strong>Advantages:</strong> Clean and fast installation, light acoustic and thermal insulation, wide variety of textures (3D, wood, stone, geometric).</p>

        <h3>Natural Stone & Exposed Brick</h3>

        <p>For those seeking rustic or industrial character. We work with limestone, slate, travertine marble, and reclaimed or high-quality artificial bricks.</p>

        <p><strong>Advantages:</strong> Uniqueness of each piece, structural resistance, timeless value, and perfect integration with natural or vintage styles.</p>

        <h3>Microcement & Stucco</h3>

        <p>Continuous, joint-free coverings that provide a minimalist, modern aesthetic. Microcement is waterproof and resistant, ideal for bathrooms and kitchens. Venetian stuccos provide shine and depth similar to polished marble.</p>

        <h2>The Professional Installation Process</h2>

        <p><strong>Phase 1: Assessment & Material Selection:</strong> We analyze the wall's condition, ambient humidity, lighting, and space usage. We advise you on the most suitable material based on your style and budget, showing you catalogs and physical samples.</p>

        <p><strong>Phase 2: Surface Preparation:</strong> A successful installation depends on a perfect base. We level, waterproof if necessary, and apply specific primers to guarantee covering adhesion.</p>

        <p><strong>Phase 3: Installation & Placement:</strong> We use high-flexibility adhesives and calibrated notched trowels. For large-format porcelain, we employ leveling systems (clips and wedges) to prevent unevenness between pieces. For wall panels, we use concealed profiles or industrial mounting adhesives.</p>

        <p><strong>Phase 4: Joints, Sealing & Finishes:</strong> We apply high-resistance epoxy or cementitious grout, seal edges and joints with neutral anti-mold silicone, and perform final cleaning with specific products that won't damage the material.</p>

        <p><strong>Phase 5: Delivery & Warranty:</strong> Joint review of the finish, delivery of material technical data sheets, and installation warranty. We explain how to maintain the covering so it preserves its beauty for years.</p>

        <h2>Applications & Design Possibilities</h2>

        <p>Wall coverings can transform any space:</p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Bathrooms:</strong> Create spa-like environments with large-format porcelain or waterproof microcement</li>
          <li><strong>Kitchens:</strong> Backsplashes that combine functionality with stunning aesthetics</li>
          <li><strong>Living Rooms:</strong> Accent walls with natural stone or 3D panels that become conversation pieces</li>
          <li><strong>Bedrooms:</strong> Headboard walls with wood-look panels or textured finishes</li>
          <li><strong>Commercial Spaces:</strong> Durable, easy-to-maintain coverings that reinforce brand identity</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Material Selection Guidance</h2>

        <p>Choosing the right covering depends on multiple factors:</p>

        <p><strong>Moisture Exposure:</strong> Bathrooms and kitchens require waterproof materials like porcelain, microcement, or specific PVC panels.</p>

        <p><strong>Traffic & Wear:</strong> High-traffic areas need scratch-resistant materials with durable finishes.</p>

        <p><strong>Maintenance Requirements:</strong> Some materials require periodic sealing or special cleaning products.</p>

        <p><strong>Budget Considerations:</strong> We offer options across different price ranges while maintaining quality standards.</p>

        <h2>Why Choose ReformaT Venezuela?</h2>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Specialists in premium materials:</strong> Certified installers for large-format porcelain and decorative systems</li>
          <li><strong>Adhesion guarantee:</strong> We use high-end adhesives and primers</li>
          <li><strong>Seamless finishes:</strong> Professional cutting and leveling technique</li>
          <li><strong>Design consultation:</strong> We help you combine materials, colors, and textures</li>
          <li><strong>Fixed-price quote:</strong> No surprises or overcharges for avoidable unforeseen events</li>
          <li><strong>Post-installation cleaning:</strong> We deliver the space ready to enjoy</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Your Next Step</h2>

        <p>If you want to renovate your walls with a modern, functional, and durable covering, the first step is a free consultation. We evaluate your space, show you real options, and deliver a detailed quote.</p>

        <p><strong>Ready to transform your walls?</strong> <a href="/en/contact">Schedule your free consultation</a> today.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-section">
    <div class="cta-wrapper">
      <h2 class="cta-title">Ready to Renovate Your Walls?</h2>
      <p class="cta-text">Schedule a free consultation and receive a detailed no-obligation quote.</p>
      <a href="/en/contact" class="btn-premium btn-primary-premium">
        <span class="btn-content">Request a Quote</span>
        <span class="btn-border"></span>
        <span class="btn-shine"></span>
        <span class="btn-arrow">→</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .article-hero { position: relative; min-height: 80vh; display: flex; align-items: flex-end; justify-content: center; text-align: center; color: var(--white); overflow: hidden; padding-top: 140px; padding-bottom: 80px; }
  .hero-bg { position: absolute; inset: 0; background-size: cover; background-position: center; z-index: 1; }
  .hero-overlay { position: absolute; inset: 0; background: linear-gradient(to top, rgba(0,0,0,0.95) 0%, rgba(0,0,0,0.4) 60%, rgba(0,0,0,0.2) 100%); z-index: 2; }
  .hero-content { position: relative; z-index: 3; max-width: 900px; padding: 0 20px; }
  .article-category { display: inline-block; background: rgba(201,169,97,0.2); border: 1px solid var(--gold); color: var(--gold); padding: 8px 20px; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 2px; margin-bottom: 25px; backdrop-filter: blur(10px); }
  .article-title { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 5rem); font-weight: 400; margin-bottom: 20px; line-height: 1.1; }
  .article-title .line { display: block; }
  .article-excerpt { font-size: 1.3rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); max-width: 700px; margin: 0 auto; line-height: 1.6; font-weight: 400; }
  .back-link { display: inline-block; color: var(--gold); font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 20px; transition: 0.3s; text-decoration: none; }
  .back-link:hover { color: var(--gold-light); }
  .article-section { padding: 80px 0; background: var(--white); }
  .article-body { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.3rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--text); }
  .article-body h2 { font-size: 2.5rem; margin: 3rem 0 1.5rem; color: var(--text); line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 500; }
  .article-body h3 { font-size: 1.8rem; margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem; color: var(--text); font-weight: 500; }
  .article-body p { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; font-weight: 400; }
  .article-body a { color: var(--gold); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gold); }
  .article-body ul, .article-body ol { margin: 1.5rem 0 1.5rem 2rem; }
  .article-body li { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; font-weight: 400; }
  .article-body img { border-radius: 12px; margin: 2.5rem 0; box-shadow: 0 15px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.08); width: 100%; }
  .article-body > p:first-of-type::first-letter { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 4.5rem; font-weight: 600; float: left; line-height: 0.75; margin-right: 0.15em; color: var(--gold); margin-top: 8px; }
  .cta-section { background: var(--bg); color: var(--white); text-align: center; padding: 110px 24px; width: 100%; }
  .cta-wrapper { max-width: 950px; margin: 0 auto; display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; }
  .cta-title { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5vw, 3.6rem); font-weight: 400; margin-bottom: 24px; line-height: 1.15; color: var(--white); text-align: center; width: 100%; }
  .cta-text { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85); max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto 45px; font-size: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.7; font-weight: 400; text-align: center; width: 100%; }
  .cta-section .btn-premium { padding: 20px 55px; font-size: 0.9rem; }
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .article-hero { min-height: 70vh; padding-top: 120px; padding-bottom: 60px; }
    .article-title { font-size: clamp(2rem, 8vw, 3.5rem); }
    .article-excerpt { font-size: 1.15rem; }
    .article-body { font-size: 1.15rem; }
    .article-body h2 { font-size: 2rem; }
    .article-body h3 { font-size: 1.5rem; }
    .cta-section { padding: 90px 20px; }
    .cta-title { font-size: 2.2rem; }
    .cta-text { font-size: 1.15rem; }
  }
</style>